headline: Palo Alto Networks slips despite Q1 beat, ByteDance valuation soars

Palo Alto Networks (PANW) stock is under pressure despite reporting fiscal first quarter earnings that beat estimates, as investors digest headlines of the company's acquisition of Chronosphere for $3.35 billion. Cipher Mining (CIFR) is reportedly raising funds in the bond market to fund its data center buildout, which is tied to Alphabet's (GOOG, GOOGL) Google, according to Bloomberg.
